Text.Value: No, you cannot leave - not without your word. Not without peace.
Every little death fills my head with more thoughts. It's too much - too painful. Kill one more of us, and you will pay.
Attack.
There are treasures. Useless to us now, but once they had value - meaning. We hid them away, untouched for a lifetime.
You kill many, but many remain. Stop. Spare our lives, or face my teeth and claws.
*Squeak!*
An ordinary rat alone. But together? Something more.
*The rat seems agitated, like it doesn't want you to leave. Not without getting what it wants.*
It shouldn't be. We should be one, long dead. Instead we are many - scurrying, hiding, surviving.
There's an infernal bounty hunter seeking Dark Justiciars. Seems he missed a target.
We are just crumbs of a life. Harmless nothings, unless you test us. Leave us in peace.
*It wants you to stop killing its fellow rats. Understandable enough.*
Attack.
The horned beast. He killed many, now you kill more. Leave us. Please.
*The rat's beady eyes hold your gaze intently. What does it want?*
Leave.
All right. Your lives for this treasure. You'd better be level with me.
*It wants for you to leave it and its fellow rats in peace.*
I am harmless - until we are cornered.
There was an infernal bounty hunter seeking Dark Justiciars. Seems he missed a target.
*Beady, malicious eyes stare at you. The rat probably wants to feast on your corpse along with its friends.*
All right - a truce, then.
Leave.
At last, you see sense. Fetch your reward and leave us. Do not come back.
*The rat sounds like it's describing Sharran rites of initiation - those of the Dark Justiciars.*
*The rat's eyes gleam with uncanny intelligence. It seems to grasp your gesture, and accept it.*
*The rat sounds like it's describing the sacred rites of Shar's Dark Justiciars.*
Fool. We gave you every opportunity, but still you choose death. So be it.
Leave.
Yell at the rat. Frighten it away.
And you better be true to your word. I am small, but we are many. Now fetch your prize, and leave.
But we all remember a name. Lyrthindor. We share who he was.
Some remember turning away from the sun. Some remember donning a black cloak. Some remember plunging a blade into an innocent heart.
Leave.
*Squeeeee!*
Remember your word - spare us, leave this place. Your reward awaits.
*The rats are describing a Dark Justiciar's memories. The orthon's quarry was here all along, scattered and hidden in plain sight.*

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This node only if the player learned of the terms of the Orthon's contract (kill all Dark justiciars)

Text.Value: Are you telling me you're one person turned into a swarm of rats? How can that be?
Scowl at the rat and shoo it away.
A final warning - offer us peace, now, or be devoured.
Study the rat. Try to figure out what it wants.
I don't usually bargain with rats. If I let you live, what's in it for me?
You're no ordinary rat, are you? None of you are.
Hold up your hands in peace.
Attack.
*The rat stares at you. It almost seems like it wants your attention.*
We only seek peace. Kill no more, and we will let you live.

Text.Value: Keep your word, and we will reveal them to you.
*Hiss!*
I'm not cutting deals with vermin. Do your worst.

Text.Value: *Squeeeak!*
*The rat watches intently, as if eager for you to leave.*
One Shar follower turned into scores of rats? How can that be?

Synopsis: The player continues to kill the rats. The rats begin to group up and attempt to bargain with the player. Their memories are starting to converge into a single consciousness of the last dark justiciar. Some players who accepted a quest from the Orthon may realise there is a Dark Justiciar in hiding, amongst these rats. If the player repeatedly talks to the rats at this point without accepting a truce, they'll turn hostile.
